
Git Documentation: https://git-scm.com/doc
Difference between git and github:
Git: 
    It is the version control software that runs locally on your machine.
    No Account registration needed.
    No internet needed
    Can use offline without touching github.

Github:
    It is service that host git repositories on the cloud.
    Easier to collaborate with other people
    Sign up an Account to use git hub.
    online place to share work using git.

Git Repo:
    A Git repo is a workspace which tracks and manages files with in a folder.
    Whenever you want to start a project or app, you need to create a git repository.